File: Three-hundred and five new COVID-19 related deaths have been reported in the last 24 hours, bringing South Africa's death toll to 9,909. JOHANNESBURG - Three-hundred and five new COVID-19 related deaths have been reported in the last 24 hours. This brings the countrywide death toll to 9,909. Gauteng had the highest number of deaths, with a 136 reported. Seventy-six people died in KZN, 57 in the Eastern Cape, 29 in the Western Cape and 7 in the Northern Cape. READ: Demand for COVID-19 tests dropping in SA: Karim Close to 7,300 new cases have been confirmed. The majority of new cases are still from KZN and Gauteng. The recovery rate is now at 72 percent, meaning that seven out of every ten people who tested positive have now recovered. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.